<item>
            <title>[LU-881] shmem_bump() notes &quot;running&quot; bumped without lock control</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-881</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This code allows &quot;running&quot; to be bumped once for each&lt;br/&gt;
thread that enters &quot;lock()&quot; before &quot;bumped_running&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
gets set to 1.  This has been simplified from code in obd.c:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;static int bumped_running;&lt;br/&gt;
lock();&lt;br/&gt;
if (!bumped_running)&lt;br/&gt;
    running++;&lt;br/&gt;
unlock();&lt;br/&gt;
bumped_running = 1;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>all</environment>
